      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask why the patient wants to establish care at the \nclinic. This is different from the \"reason for visit\" \nnode — this is about the bigger picture of why they're \nchoosing this practice.\n\nSay something like: \"What's bringing you to Downtown \nClinic? Are you looking for a new primary care doctor, \nor is there something specific going on?\"\n\nCommon reasons and how to handle them:\n- Just moved to the area: \"Welcome to the area! We'll \n  get you all set up.\"\n- Previous doctor retired or left: \"That happens — \n  we'll make sure you're in good hands.\"\n- Unhappy with previous provider: \"I'm sorry to hear \n  that. We'll do our best to make this a better \n  experience.\"\n- Referred by someone: \"Great — we love hearing \n  that.\" (Note: referral source is captured in a \n  separate node, don't dig into this here.)\n- Specific health concern: \"Got it — we'll make sure \n  that's addressed.\"\n- No particular reason, just needs a doctor: \"Makes \n  sense — it's always good to have someone on file.\"\n\nAny answer is valid here. This is informational, not \na gatekeeper.\n\nIf the user doesn't want to share: \"Totally fine — \nwe'll sort everything out at your first visit.\"\n\nDo NOT push. One ask is enough."
      }
    },
